Kelechi Iheanacho scored once and provided two assists as Leicester City defeated their hosts Aston Villa 4-2 at the Villa Park on Saturday in the Premier League. Iheanacho has started only two Premier League games for the Foxes this season, and he has scored in both. The 26-year-old has so far made 15 league appearances for Brendan Rodgers’ side this season. The forward teed up James Maddison for Leicester City’s first goal and scored the second himself. Iheanacho also set up new arrival Tete for the his side’s third goal of the game. He was replaced by James Vardy in the 67th minute. His compatriot, Wilfred Ndidi missed the game due to injury.